quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  13,19,"So, is he who knows that what has been sent down to you from your Lord is the Truth, like him who is blind? Surely only the ones endowed with intellects do remind themselves"
  13,20,Who fulfil the covenant of Allah and do not break the compact
  13,21,"And who hold together what Allah has commanded to be held together, and are apprehensive of their Lord, and fear an odious reckoning"
  13,22,"And who (endure) patiently seeking the Face of their Lord, and keep up the prayer, and expend of whatever We have provided them, secretly and in public, and who parry an odious (act) with a fair one; those will have the (Ultimate) Outcome of the Residence"
  13,23,"Gardens of Adn, (Eden) which they will enter, and the ones who were righteous of their fathers and their spouses and their off springs (will enter too); and the Angels will enter to them from every gate"
  13,24,"Peace be upon you, for that you endured patiently.\" So favorable is the (Ultimate) Outcome of the Residence"
  13,25,"And the ones who break the covenant of Allah even after His compact, and cut (off) what Allah has commanded to be held together, and who corrupt in the earth, those will have the curse and they will have an odious Residence"
  13,26,"Allah outspreads the provision for whomever He decides and determines (it); and they exult with (the present) life; (Literally: the lowly \"life\", i.e., the life of this world) and in no way is the present life, beside the Hereafter, (anything) except a (passing) enjoyment (Literally: belongings)"
  13,27,"And the ones who have disbelieved say, \"If only a sign had been sent down upon him from his Lord!\" Say, \"Surely Allah leads into error whomever He decides and He guides to Him whomever has turned penitent"
  13,28,The ones who have believed and whose hearts (feel) composed with the Remembrance of Allah -verily in the Remembrance of Allah the hearts are composed